  "description": [
    "TESTIMONIAL FOR I REV 0 SCNELLINGER Rev Gerard Schellinger pastor of St Patricks church who left Wednes day to accept a call at Rawlins was given a delightful informal farewell party by his parishioners at the church rectory Tuesday evening which was well attended and thoroughly en joyed by all The ladies of the parish had quietly gone about raising a fund with which to purchase a fitting gift for their pastor and had decided on a beautiful solid leather suitcase which was pre sented to Father Schellinger together with a purse of S9O which was the amount left over after the present was bought The presentation soeech was made by P J Quealy who spoke of the regret with which the departure of the pastor was viewed by all and Father Schellinger responded feeling ly saying that while he considered his new assignment in the nature of a promotion which he appreciated he had formed many warm friendships in and around Kemmerer which he was finding it hard to sever Three visiting priests who were in the city visiting Father Schellinger and saying farewell were also called upoh and each responded briefly and in a happy vein These were"
